<DOC><DOCNO> AP891018-0215 </DOCNO><FILEID>AP-NR-10-18-89 2053EDT</FILEID><FIRST>r i AM-NorthernIreland     10-18 0181</FIRST><SECOND>AM-Northern Ireland,0188</SECOND><HEAD>Protestant Shot to Death at Door, IRA Claims Responsibility</HEAD><DATELINE>BELFAST, Northern Ireland (AP) </DATELINE><TEXT>   Three men shot to death aProtestant in front of his family in an outlying village lateWednesday, and the IRA claimed responsibility.   The victim, who was not immediately identified, was killed athis home in Magheralin, a village 17 miles southwest of Belfast,when he answered a knock at the door, city police headquarters saidin a statement.   Police said the victim's wife and teen-age daughter witnessedthe killing.   The gunmen used a stolen car, which was later found burned outfive miles from the scene of the attack, police said. However, theygave few other details.   The mainly Roman Catholic Irish Republican Army claimedresponsibility in a message to Belfast news organizations.   It said the victim was a key figure among Protestantparamilitary groups. The statement said he had been involved inattacks on Catholic targets.   The IRA is fighting British rule in Northern Ireland. It wantsto unite the predominantly Protestant province with the 95 percentCatholic Republic of Ireland.</TEXT></DOC>